OL,3,C'A stain on society': Over 3 million
OL,4,Cfood bank parcels handed out in record
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FVal McKie, a former management
OL,8,Fconsultant from the North West, found
OL,9,Fherself needing to use food banks
OL,10,Fafter her husband died, her contractor
OL,11,Fclosing down, and her landlord selling
OL,12,Fher home.
OL,14,FShe says she was "overwhelmed with
OL,15,Fshame" at having to use food banks,
OL,16,Fdescribing the increasing need for
OL,17,Fmore food banks as "a stain on our
OL,18,Fsociety."
